    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-10-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <head>160. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d160fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, AE 6. Confidential; <gloss
                            target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>. Drafted by Malcolm Toon (<gloss
                            target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_SOV1">SOV</gloss>) on
                        October 18 and cleared in <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss> and <gloss
                            target="#t_S1">S</gloss> on October 19. Regarding the location and time
                        of this conversation, see <ref target="#d158fn1">footnote 1, Document
                            158</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1966-10-10">October 10,
                            1966</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Plowshare</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">U.S.</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>The Secretary</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FWC2">William C. Foster</persName>—<gloss
                                    target="#t_ACDA1">ACDA</gloss>
                            </item>
                            <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TLET1">Llewellyn
                                    Thompson</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Governor <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LJM2">John M. Leddy</persName>—<gloss
                                    target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>
                            </item>
                            <item>Malcolm Toon—<gloss target="#t_SOV1">SOV</gloss>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>
                        </hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Soviet Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Anatoliy
                                    Dobrynin</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Alexander I. Zinchuk, Minister-Counselor, Soviet Embassy</item>
                            <item>Counselor of Embassy Vorontsov</item>
                            <item>Ivan I. Ippolitov, Aide to <persName corresp="#p_GAA1"
                                    >Gromyko</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>After the dinner meeting Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName>
                    raised with the Secretary the idea of exchanging views on peaceful uses
                    explosions. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> referred to the
                    Secretary’s discussion on this matter with <persName corresp="#p_DAF1"
                        >Dobrynin</persName> some time ago<note n="2" xml:id="d160fn2">
                        <ref target="#d123">Document 123</ref>.</note> and asked where we should go
                    from here. The Secretary said we would be prepared to set up a small group of
                    experts to focus on the problem and Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TLET1"
                        >Thompson</persName> could discuss the matter further with Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName>. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> said that the Soviets were indeed
                    interested in going forward with such an exchange of views and the arrangement
                    suggested by the Secretary would be entirely acceptable.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
